title: Russia Rejoins Grain Deal, but Warns It Could Pull Out Again
description: The agreement allows Ukraine, a major food producer, to export grain by sea, easing the threat of famine in other countries.
dc:creator: Ivan Nechepurenko and Matthew Mpoke Bigg

media:content.media:description: The Malta-flagged bulk carrier Zante transiting the Bosporus on Wednesday en route to Belgium while carrying over 52,000 tons of rapeseed from Ukraine.
